title: For Sale/Trade:  Argentine Naval FN-49 SAFN .308 7.62x51
postcontent:
"The Argentine FN-49s were originally made in 7.65mm.

The Argentine Navy received many of these. The navy rifles are marked “ARA”(Armada Republica Argentina) next to the Argentine crest on the receiver. In the early 1960s the Argentine Navy converted their FN-49s to 7.62mm Nato. This was done by installing a new barrel. At the same time they were modified to use a detachable magazine. This was a 20-round magazine that resembles a FN-FAL magazine but it is not interchangeable. This was the only official conversion of the SAFN to use a detachable magazine.

Some (Very Few) Argentine Navy FN-49s were imported to the U.S. in the 1990s.

The 20-round magazines were shortened to hold 10 rounds to make them compliant with the Clinton-era high-capacity magazine ban. These guns also had the muzzle cap welded in place so an evil flash hider could not be installed. A few years after the magazines were shortened, the government changed the interpretation of the import rules to allow standard-capacity magazines to come in if they were made before 1994. There are now some 20-round magazines available." (GunDigest)

---------------------------------------------------

Absolutely beautiful and rare Argentine Naval contract F-49 in .308 with 3 20rd mags and 1 10rd mag.  Shoots like a dream, looks like a dream, and is all matching with ARA stamp.  Internals are clean as a whistle, this thing is built like a tank, and barrel looks great!

I am not pressed to sell/trade this rifle, but if the right offer presents itself then I could use the cash to pay for school.

title: For Sale:  Sig P229 Elite Dark - Grayguns Action Enhancement - 5 Mags
postcontent:
I am selling my Sig Sauer P229 Elite Dark in .40 S&W.  I am selling it due to moving to .45 ACP, not because of anything wrong with this gun.  Honestly, this is one of the nicest Sigs you'll see for sale.

You can look up the factory specifics on the gun here:  http://www.sigsauer.com/CatalogProductDetails/p229-elite-dark.aspx

I didn't think I'd like the beavertail, but I loved it.  It actually isn't a problem for concealed carry.  What's really special about this P229 is the work done by Grayguns out of Oregon.  Simple google searching about Grayguns will lead you to forums where you will learn it is the most highly respected Sig gunsmith shop in the country.

I had three actions performed on the P229 by Grayguns late last year.  The action enhancement package was done, which basically means spring swaps were done (but not too extreme to make light primer strikes) and all trigger parts were polished and improved as much as possible.  There is a short trigger installed on it (short length, not SRT).  Finally, since the Elite Dark Sigs come with horrible adjustable rear sights, a fixed rear sight was installed.  The rear sight is completely black (I'm never going back to three-dot) and has a smaller than average notch, and the front sight is fresh tritium.

The result is the best-pointing, most comfortable Sig with the fastest shots on target.  Other awesome shit about the gun include the great Short Reset Trigger, great feeling Sig thin aluminum grips, beefy extractor, and front cocking serrations.

With the gun I will include:

- Small case
- FIVE .40/.357sig magazines, all great condition
- Old short trigger that used to be on it
- Optional:  Galco IWB Royal Guard II holster for P229R in great condition

Full discretion.  I used this full time on duty and off as a police officer.  Best estimate is around 1500-180 rounds.  It therefore has some holster wear and some light wear on the top of the barrel, but everything has been cared for.  I'm attaching a picture showing the sights and the top of the barrel.  I use the best grease money can buy for slide rails and keep the other moving parts lubed appropriately.  I've never had a malfunction with it.

If you prefer 9mm, the Bar-Sto or EFK conversion barrels have great reviews and I've read you can use the 9mm in the Sig .40 mags with no issues, but I haven't tried that.

Email me with any questions or offers.  I'm willing to ship, but prefer to meet.
